            </span>
            <span class="utterance" who="#josephyK" start="2324.270" end="x">Ich bin nach Paris zurück gekehrt, ich, eh, habe Arbeit bei den amerikanischen Okkupationsbehörden gefunden, meine Frau ist in der Schneiderei tätig, das ist ja ihr Beruf, wir haben endlich unser Kind bei uns und so leben wir nach wie vor ...</span>
        </li>
                <li>
            <span class="who">
                <span class="">David Boder</span>:
            </span>
            <span class="utterance" who="#boderD" start="x" end="x">Ja ...</span>
        </li>
                <li>
            <span class="who">
                <span class="">Karl Josephy</span>:
            </span>
            <span class="utterance" who="#josephyK" start="2340.595" end="x">...von unserer Arbeit.</span>
        </li>
                <li>
            <span class="who">
                <span class="">David Boder</span>:
            </span>
            <span class="utterance" who="#boderD" start="2344.490" end="x">[In English] Also, this concludes Spool 66 of Mr. Karl Josephy who gave us his story from the internment in Africa and to minute to pass the whole time of occupation here in France as a qualified worker. Paris, August the 23, 1946, Illinois Institute of Technology wire recording.</span>
        </li>
                <li>
            <span class="who">
                <span class="">Karl Josephy</span>:
            </span>
            <span class="utterance" who="#josephyK" start="2374.255" end="x">Bon.</span>
        </li>
            </ul>
    <ol class="notes">
                
